00:47:41,820 --> 00:47:46,110
and that question directed you to a certain part of reality.
那个问题让你注意现实的某一部分

864
00:47:46,350 --> 00:47:47,240
And that's a good thing.
这是件好事

865
00:47:47,460 --> 00:47:50,350
Because if we were focusing on everything all the time,
因为如果我们总是专注于一切事情

866
00:47:50,590 --> 00:47:51,820
that wouldn't be a good thing.
那就不是件好事

867
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:54,310
We would be distracted by every single noise,
每种噪音都会让我们分心

868
00:47:54,500 --> 00:47:55,900
by every single movement.
所有物体运动都会让我们分心

869
00:47:56,520 --> 00:47:57,880
So it's a good thing that we can focus.
所以我们能集中注意力是件好事

870
00:47:58,070 --> 00:48:00,230
However,we also need to remember
但是 我们也要记得

871
00:48:00,500 --> 00:48:03,560
the consequences of this ability to focus
这种集中精神的能力带来的后果

872
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:07,740
that is not always good it's not always helpful.
却不总是好事或者有益的

873
00:48:09,530 --> 00:48:12,310
Because as far as you were concerned,
因为在你们看来

874
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:14,470
there were no children on the bus.
巴士上没有小孩

875
00:48:15,550 --> 00:48:16,910
As far as you were concerned,
在你们看来

876
00:48:17,150 --> 00:48:18,150
there were only geometric shapes.
上面只有几何图形

877
00:48:18,350 --> 00:48:20,060
In other words,my question,for most of you,
换句话说 我的问题给你们大多数人

878
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:22,760
created a very specific reality,
制造了一种特定的现实

879
00:48:24,090 --> 00:48:26,770
a reality which there were geometric shapes
一种只有几何图形

880
00:48:27,350 --> 00:48:31,050
and no children on the bus.
巴士上没有小孩的现实

881
00:48:31,490 --> 00:48:33,950
Now that has very important implications.
这有着非常重要的含义

882
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:40,460
Think about the following question: what question is mostly asked
想想以下的问题 蜜月期过后

883
00:48:40,890 --> 00:48:45,430
by couples beyond the honeymoon phase?
夫妻间问的最多的问题是什么?

884
00:48:45,650 --> 00:48:46,900
so they go through the honeymoon phase
他们度过蜜月期之后

885
00:48:47,100 --> 00:48:49,690
whether it's a month,a year or sometimes two years.
不管是一个月 一年还是两年

886
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:53,150
What questions do they begin to ask after that period of time?
那段时期后他们会开始问什么问题?

887
00:48:54,500 --> 00:48:56,470
"What's wrong? What's not working?
"怎么回事?有什么问题?"

888
00:48:56,690 --> 00:48:58,660
How can we improve the relationship?"
"我们怎样去改善关系?'

889
00:48:58,920 --> 00:49:01,140
Now that's a very important question to ask.
这是一个非常重要的问题

890
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:02,130
Very important.
非常重要

891
00:49:02,340 --> 00:49:03,730
But if that's the only question
但如果这是我们所问的

892
00:49:03,950 --> 00:49:05,760
or the only questions that we ask,
唯一一些问题

893
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:11,230
then that is the only thing we will see.
那么我们看到的也只有这件事

894
00:49:13,470 --> 00:49:15,990
The only things that we will see are our deficiencies,
我们能看到的只是我们的不足

895
00:49:16,220 --> 00:49:17,780
the things that are not working,
出了差错的事情

896
00:49:18,040 --> 00:49:19,100
the things that need to be improved,
需要去改善的事情

897
00:49:19,350 --> 00:49:21,440
the weaknesses of my partner,
我伴侣的缺点

898
00:49:21,710 --> 00:49:22,810
of the relationship.
我们关系的缺点

899
00:49:23,080 --> 00:49:26,640
If the only questions that I ask are "what is not working",
如果我只是问"什么出了差错"

900
00:49:27,090 --> 00:49:29,730
"what's wrong","what do I need to improve"-- and again,
"怎么回事 我要改善什么" 重申一次

901
00:49:29,950 --> 00:49:31,690
these are not questions we need to do away with,
我们不需要去掉这些问题

902
00:49:31,990 --> 00:49:35,550
they are important. However if they are the only questions,
它们很重要 但如果它们是唯一的问题

903
00:49:35,720 --> 00:49:37,820
and usually they are the only questions
而通常它们确实是

904
00:49:38,090 --> 00:49:40,200
that are asked or primarily asked,
被提出或主要提出的问题

905
00:49:40,430 --> 00:49:44,690
then as far as the couple is concerned,not objectively,
那么在这对夫妇看来 不是客观上

906
00:49:44,930 --> 00:49:46,630
but as far as the couple is concerned,
在这对夫妇看来

907
00:49:46,910 --> 00:49:50,290
good things do not exist in the relationship.
他们的关系里没有好的事物

908
00:49:50,510 --> 00:49:52,320
Just like as far as you are concerned,
就像在你们看来

909
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:54,530
there were no children on the bus,
巴士上没有小孩

910
00:49:54,770 --> 00:49:57,060
even though they were right there in front of you,
虽然他们就在你们面前

911
00:49:57,300 --> 00:49:58,510
staring at you.
盯着你

912
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:02,990
But they do not exist.
但是他们不存在

913
00:50:04,870 --> 00:50:06,710
Or think about it at an individual level.
或者从个人的角度思考它

914
00:50:06,890 --> 00:50:07,720
This is very important.
这非常重要

915
00:50:07,950 --> 00:50:09,530
What is the question that we,
我们问得最多的问题...

916
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:14,260
most Americans,most Australians,most Chinese,
大多数美国人 澳大利亚人 中国人

917
00:50:14,480 --> 00:50:17,980
most Israelis,most Europeans,Africans--
以色列人 欧洲人 非洲人

918
00:50:18,200 --> 00:50:21,110
what is the question that is mostly asked about the self?
大多数人最经常问自己的是什么问题?

919
00:50:21,330 --> 00:50:23,270
And the reason why I mentioned all these places
我之所以要提到那些地方

920
00:50:23,460 --> 00:50:25,400
is because this is cross-cultural study.
是因为这是跨文化的研究

921
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:28,720
People mostly ask themselves,
大多数人都会问自己

922
00:50:29,050 --> 00:50:33,480
"what are my weaknesses? What do I need to improve?"
我的弱点是什么?我要改善什么?

923
00:50:33,750 --> 00:50:35,410
Very often to the exclusion of
通常排除了

924
00:50:35,650 --> 00:50:39,990
"what are my strengths? What are my virtues? What am I good at?"
我的长处是什么?我擅长于什么?

925
00:50:40,290 --> 00:50:42,080
And if the only question
如果我们问自己的

926
00:50:42,530 --> 00:50:46,600
that we ask ourselves are the only questions that are
唯一问题是

927
00:50:46,780 --> 00:50:49,160
"what are my weaknesses? Deficiencies?",
我的缺点 我的不足是什么?

928
00:50:50,650 --> 00:50:52,650
then the only thing we'll see in ourselves
那么我们能看到的

929
00:50:52,930 --> 00:50:55,000
are weaknesses and deficiencies.
只有自己的缺点和不足

930
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,300
And as far as we are concerned,
在我们看来

931
00:50:57,550 --> 00:51:01,530
the good things-- our strengths,our passions,our virtues--
好的东西 我们的长处 热情 美德

932
00:51:02,610 --> 00:51:07,380
the wonderful things within us do not exist.
我们身上的美好事物并不存在

933
00:51:07,700 --> 00:51:09,880
Just like as far as you are concerned,
就像在你们看来

934
00:51:10,130 --> 00:51:12,220
the children on the bus did not exist.
巴士上的小孩并不存在

935
00:51:12,830 --> 00:51:13,620
Now I ask you,
现在我问你们

936
00:51:14,110 --> 00:51:17,910
could a person who only or primarily focuses on weaknesses
一个主要关注缺点的人

937
00:51:19,380 --> 00:51:20,400
and does not see,
看不到

938
00:51:20,640 --> 00:51:23,710
does not appreciate their strength,their passions,
也不欣赏他们的长处 热情

939
00:51:23,940 --> 00:51:24,740
their virtues--
他们的美德的人

940
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:30,330
can a person like that experience high levels of self-respect,
一个这样的人会有很高的自尊心

941
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:35,580
self-confidence,happiness?
自信心和很多的快乐吗?

942
00:51:37,440 --> 00:51:41,810
And we wonder,why do so many relationships fail?
我们还奇怪 为什么这么多婚姻会失败?

943
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:48,280
And we wonder,why depression,anxiety
我们还奇怪 为什么抑郁 焦虑

944
00:51:48,490 --> 00:51:51,820
and low self-esteem are increasing so much?
以及自尊心低落的情况增加了这么多?

945
00:51:52,430 --> 00:51:53,990
The intentions are there.
动机是有的

946
00:51:54,210 --> 00:51:55,050
They are good. We are asking
它们都是好的动机 我们问的是

947
00:51:55,220 --> 00:51:58,500
"How can we improve? What can we do better?"
"我们如何改善?怎样才能做得更好?"

948
00:51:59,180 --> 00:52:02,990
But if we don't also ask the positive question,
但如果我们不问积极的问题

949
00:52:03,250 --> 00:52:06,360
that part of reality will not exist as far as we are concerned.
在我们看来那部分现实并不存在

950
00:52:06,700 --> 00:52:09,370
Just like for the psychologists for decade,
就像数十年来对那些心理学家一样

951
00:52:09,670 --> 00:52:13,620
the answer to their questions,the solution to the problem
他们问题的答案 问题的解决方案

952
00:52:13,840 --> 00:52:16,450
that they wanted to solve did not exist,
并不存在

953
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:17,790
even though it is right there,
即使它就在那里

954
00:52:18,010 --> 00:52:21,280
in front of their very eyes within the successful kids,
在他们的眼前 在那些成功孩子的身上

955
00:52:21,780 --> 00:52:22,800
within their resilience.
在他们的心理弹性里

956
00:52:23,050 --> 00:52:25,750
Questions create reality.
问题缔造现实

957
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:28,770
The questions we ask very often determine
我们所问的问题通常决定了

958
00:52:29,590 --> 00:52:31,280
the quest that we will pursue,
我们追求的东西

959
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:32,600
the path that we will take,
我们会走的道路

960
00:52:32,850 --> 00:52:33,870
the life that we will lead,
我们会过的生活

961
00:52:34,110 --> 00:52:35,130
whether it's individually,
不管是从个人方面来说

962
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,600
whether it's interpersonally,
从人际关系方面来说

963
00:52:37,330 --> 00:52:38,700
whether it's organizationally.
从组织方面来说都是这样

964
00:52:38,960 --> 00:52:39,620
What is the question?
什么问题...

965
00:52:39,860 --> 00:52:41,890
Many of you I know are going into consulting.
我知道你们很多会要当心理辅导师

966
00:52:42,680 --> 00:52:45,040
What's the question that most consultants ask,
心理辅导师最经常问的问题是什么?

967
00:52:45,240 --> 00:52:47,460
Either explicit question or implicit question,
不管他们是否说出来

968
00:52:47,710 --> 00:52:49,440
the first time when they meet a client?
他们首次见到客户问的问题是什么?

969
00:52:50,310 --> 00:52:53,870
--"What's wrong? What can we improve?
"有什么问题?有什么需要改善的?"

970
00:52:54,140 --> 00:52:56,320
What are the weaknesses that we need to strengthen them?"
"有什么缺点需要改正?"

971
00:52:56,560 --> 00:52:59,310
Again,important questions to ask.
再说一次 它们是很重要的问题

972
00:52:59,550 --> 00:53:01,400
But if you only ask these questions,
但如果你只问这些问题

973
00:53:01,690 --> 00:53:02,890
then you are ignoring the strengths,
那么你就忽视了这个机构的

974
00:53:03,110 --> 00:53:07,620
the virtues of the organization.
优势以及美德

975
00:53:07,880 --> 00:53:09,450
And what you are doing,you are enervating,
你所做的只是在让他们失去活力

976
00:53:09,660 --> 00:53:12,040
you are weakening the organization over time.
你在让公司慢慢地变弱

977
00:53:12,330 --> 00:53:15,030
It is as important,if not more important,
欣赏起作用的东西

978
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:17,700
to also appreciate what is working,
也同样重要 如果不是更重要的话

979
00:53:17,980 --> 00:53:21,550
organizationally,interpersonally,as well as individually.
不管是在机构里 人际关系里或个人方面

980
00:53:22,280 --> 00:53:24,600
It is important to appreciate what is good.
欣赏好的事物非常重要

981
00:53:24,830 --> 00:53:26,800
I mean,look at the word,"appreciate".
看看"Appreciate"这个词

982
00:53:27,040 --> 00:53:29,850
Two meanings: first meaning-- to say thank you for something,
它有两个意思 其一就是为某事感激

983
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:31,480
not to take it for granted.
而不是认为某事理所当然

984
00:53:31,770 --> 00:53:32,410
And that's a nice thing to do.
这样做很好

985
00:53:32,610 --> 00:53:36,150
We shouldn't take for granted our virtues,our successes.
我们不应该把长处 成功看作理所当然

986
00:53:36,470 --> 00:53:38,630
We shouldn't take for granted others.
我们不应把别人看作理所当然

987
00:53:39,110 --> 00:53:40,200
That's a nice thing to do.
这是很好的事情

988
00:53:40,460 --> 00:53:44,450
But appreciate has a second meaning,which is to grow.
但是"Appreciate"还有一个意思就是增值

989
00:53:44,680 --> 00:53:46,310
Money appreciates in the bank.
钱在银行里会增值

990
00:53:46,540 --> 00:53:48,180
The economy hopefully appreciates.
经济会增长

991
00:53:49,880 --> 00:53:51,660
When we appreciate the good,
当我们感激好的东西

992
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:55,830
the good appreciates-- the good grows.
好的东西便会增值 它会增长

993
00:53:57,030 --> 00:54:01,240
Unfortunately,the other side of the same coin applies as well.
不幸的是 反过来也是成立的

994
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:03,070
When we don't appreciate the good,
当我们不感激好的东西

995
00:54:03,290 --> 00:54:08,290
when we take it for granted,the good depreciates.
把它看作理所当然 好的东西会贬值

996
00:54:10,540 --> 00:54:12,420
And that's what happens in most relationships
那就是大多数婚姻

997
00:54:12,650 --> 00:54:14,100
after the honeymoon phase.
蜜月期后发生的情况

998
00:54:14,330 --> 00:54:15,410
That's what happens to most people,
那就是发生在多数人身上的情况

999
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:17,860
especially to very driven people who want to improve,
特别是对于那些有动力去提高

1000
00:54:18,130 --> 00:54:19,180
who want to get better.
想变得更好的人

1001
00:54:19,430 --> 00:54:20,700
And that's good thing,
那是件好事

1002
00:54:21,750 --> 00:54:23,140
if that is what makes you happy.
如果那让你感到开心的话

1003
00:54:23,390 --> 00:54:24,050
At the same time,
同时

1004
00:54:24,370 --> 00:54:29,540
it's equally important to also appreciate what is good inside me
欣赏自己的优点也同样重要

1005
00:54:30,750 --> 00:54:32,600
what my strengths,what my virtues are.
我的长处 优点是什么

1006
00:54:32,920 --> 00:54:34,830
And we are going to do a lot of that in the course.
我们在课堂中将经常练习这点

1007
00:54:35,080 --> 00:54:37,680
And again,not to go to the point of narcissism.
但是不会做到自我陶醉的程度

1008
00:54:37,920 --> 00:54:40,930
If anything narcissism-- and we'll talk about it
我们会谈到自我陶醉

1009
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:42,930
in the second last lecture in the semester-
就在本学期倒数第二节课

1010
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:46,740
narcissism is not about self-confidence,about self-esteem.
自我陶醉不是自信 不是自尊

1011
00:54:46,980 --> 00:54:48,040
It's exactly the opposite.
它正好相反

1012
00:54:48,910 --> 00:54:51,420
We are talking about grounded self-confidence.
我们说的是有根据的自信

1013
00:54:51,980 --> 00:54:54,750
Grounded,generous,benevolent happiness.
有根据的大方有益的快乐

1014
00:54:55,610 --> 00:54:57,190
In order to lead that kind of life,
为了过上那种生活

1015
00:54:57,470 --> 00:54:58,940
we need to also appreciate what is working,
我们还要欣赏起作用的东西

1016
00:54:59,290 --> 00:55:04,000
to also focus on,metaphorically speaking,the children on a bus.
用比喻的意义上说 还要留意巴士上的小孩

1017
00:55:06,090 --> 00:55:09,300
Stavros and Torres in the wonderful book on relationships,
Stavros和Torres在一本关于婚姻的好书里说

1018
00:55:09,650 --> 00:55:11,370
"We see what we look for and we miss much of
"我们会看到要寻找的东西"

1019
00:55:11,590 --> 00:55:14,480
what we are not looking for even though it is there.
"错失不去寻找的东西 虽然它在那里"

1020
00:55:14,910 --> 00:55:17,900
Our experience of the world is heavily influenced
"我们的阅历"

1021
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:20,620
by where we place our attention."
"被我们的关注点深深地影响了"

1022
00:55:23,110 --> 00:55:26,590
Questions very often create reality.
问题经常会缔造现实

1023
00:55:28,270 --> 00:55:32,030
The first important thing to understand about questions
理解什么是问题的首要事情

1024
00:55:32,240 --> 00:55:35,770
is that we need to understand the questions.
就是我们要理解那些问题

1025
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:39,010
And here I want to defer to a very important philosopher,
在这点我同意一位重要哲学家

1026
00:55:39,920 --> 00:55:42,280
a 20th and 21st century philosopher,
一位20世纪和21世纪的哲学家

1027
00:55:43,690 --> 00:55:47,530
who illustrates the importance of understanding questions--
他阐明了理解问题的重要性

